  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is a multicentre, randomized, placebo-controlled, fully blinded, clinical trial of
      twice daily oral valacyclovir 500mg versus placebo with the goal of delaying the need for
      initiating HAART among HIV infected individuals who neither use nor require HAART, and who
      have not used chronic suppressive anti-HSV therapy for at least the 6 months prior to study
      initiation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
